HEADWORD: Ablaqueation
<hw>Ab*la`que*a"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ablaqueatio</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act or process of laying bare
the roots of trees to expose them to the air and water.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Evelyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

